From: Alex Stewart <alex.stewart@ni.com>
Date: Wed, 12 May 2021 08:03:37 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] CMakeLists: only link win64 on windows

Adding a link to ./imports/lib/win64 is not sane to do on Linux builds;
restrict it to the WIN32-build-case.

Signed-off-by: Alex Stewart <alex.stewart@ni.com>

Upstream-Status: Pending

---
 CMakeLists.txt | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
index 3081b59..df0f980 100644
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -56,7 +56,9 @@ include_directories(
   "./imports/include"
   "./source"
 )
-link_directories("./imports/lib/win64")
+if(WIN32)
+  link_directories("./imports/lib/win64")
+endif()
 
